    <question>
        <stimulus>"The Federal Reserve Act is the most important piece of financial legislation which has been enacted... It provides machinery for free and elastic movements of credit."
- Woodrow Wilson, Statement on signing the Federal Reserve Act, 1913</stimulus>
        <prompt>The primary purpose of this legislation was to:</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Regulate the stock market</option>
            <option letter="b">Stabilize the banking system</option>
            <option letter="c">Break up monopolies</option>
            <option letter="d">Establish income tax</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The Federal Reserve Act created a central banking system to stabilize the nation's money supply and prevent banking panics, a key Progressive Era economic reform.</explanation>
